    <h2>Attraction Descriptions</h2>
    <h3>Hanoi</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Ho Chi Minh Mausoleum:</strong> The final resting place of Vietnam's revolutionary leader.</li>
        <li><strong>One Pillar Pagoda:</strong> A historic Buddhist temple built in 1049.</li>
        <li><strong>Temple of Literature:</strong> Vietnam's first national university, dedicated to Confucius.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Ha Long Bay</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Limestone Karsts:</strong> Towering limestone formations rising from emerald waters.</li>
        <li><strong>Surprise Cave (Sung Sot Cave):</strong> One of the largest and most beautiful caves in the bay.</li>
        <li><strong>Titov Island:</strong> Offers panoramic views after a short hike.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Ninh Binh</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Hoa Lu Ancient Capital:</strong> The capital of Vietnam in the 10th and 11th centuries.</li>
        <li><strong>Tam Coc:</strong> Known as "Ha Long Bay on land" with scenic boat rides through rice paddies.</li>
        <li><strong>Bich Dong Pagoda:</strong> A series of pagodas built into a mountainside.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Essential Vietnamese Phrases</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><span class="phrase">Hello:</span> Xin chào (sin chow)</li>
        <li><span class="phrase">Thank you:</span> Cảm ơn (gahm un)</li>
        <li><span class="phrase">Yes:</span> Vâng (vuhng)</li>
        <li><span class="phrase">No:</span> Không (kohng)</li>
        <li><span class="phrase">How much is this?:</span> Cái này bao nhiêu tiền? (guy nye baow nyew tee-un?)</li>
        <li><span class="phrase">Where is the restroom?:</span> Nhà vệ sinh ở đâu? (nya vay
